commentary: Shafiul Islam to Mohammad Hafeez, OUT typical slow-pitch dismissal. Hafeez is gone to a soft shot. Short, wide, and painfully sluggish. The ball rises in slow motion, and Hafeez is already through his punch into the covers when it comes through. He lobs it amiably into the covers off the bat toe, and makes his way back. Bangladesh are thrilled.

commentary: Shafiul Islam to Asad Shafiq, FOUR runs uppish but safe. Expect a lot of those today. It was pitched up, but wasn't exactly a half-volley. A yard or so fuller than the ball that consumed Hafeez, and Shafiq planted the front foot across and smote it through the line. It stopped on him, but there was no stopping his bat swing. Clean and crisp over the covers.

commentary: Shafiul Islam to Younis Khan, (no ball) FOUR runs It's all happening at the ZACS! No-ball, edge, doesn't carry to the keeper, runs away for four, and a free-hit to follow. Shafiul changes the angle, goes very wide and has in fact cut the return crease. Younis goes at it hard-handed, away from the body and gets a healthy edge, but it drops well short of slip on this pitch. He parries it away and it runs through to the third man fence.

commentary: Shakib Al Hasan to Asad Shafiq, no run big spin and a stumping appeal goes upstairs. Classic stuff from Shakib, this. He tosses it up invitingly outside off, it curves in and breaks it away. Shafiq is lured into the trap, he goes for the drive and drags his back foot out of the crease. The ball spins past the edge and goes into Rahim's gloves. He seemed to take an extra moment to gather and break the stumps. Shafiq had the chance to push the toe back in, but he might be on the line... The umpire's taking a close look at this. It's a matter of millimetres. Probably microns. He gets the benefit of doubt.

commentary: Shakib Al Hasan to Asad Shafiq, OUT lovely, lovely bowling! Shafiq is gone, there's no benefit of doubt to be had when the stumps are broken. He's set him up with a series of balls that spun sharply, and now sends down the armer from slightly wide of the crease. Shafiq is lulled into a loose drive off the front foot. The ball drops in front of him and shoots straight through bat-pad gap. All over.

commentary: Mahmudullah to Sohail Tanvir, OUT Tanvir goes to cut and it's a feather-edge through to the keeper. Rahim stays low and composed to complete a very good catch, he didn't have much time to react.

commentary: Mahmudullah to Umar Gul, OUT another one bites the dust! Mahmudullah is on a hat-trick, as is Rahim, and Pakistan are nine down. That one didn't turn in much as Gul prodded forward and felt for it, it just slid along and took the outside edge. Rahim's day is getting better and better. Mahmudullah is chuffed - no bowling for 44 overs, and then two scalps in four balls.

commentary: Mahmudullah to Abdur Rehman, OUT all over! The umpire's finger went up in a hurry. Rehman looked completely plumb there. Mahmudullah has rolled out the tail in seven balls. He angled this in from round the stumps, and got it to straighten past the forward prod and thud into the pad low and in front of middle and off.

commentary: Mohammad Hafeez to Tamim Iqbal, OUT Hafeez has again got Tamim for a duck! This is uncanny! Devon Smith will have his sympathies for Tamim. This one turned. It angled in, landed on off and straightened ever so slightly. Tamim was forward and solid in defence, but down the wrong line. The ball slipped past and hit off stump.

commentary: Abdur Rehman to Mushfiqur Rahim, OUT Horror stroke! Plumb in front. Bangladesh are spinning out of control. Angled in from wide of the crease, it lands on off and straightens. The ball deceived Rahim in flight, it was a touch fuller than he thought as he stayed back and shaped to paddle it away. The ball slipped past and hit him in front of off. Was that doing too much? Umpire Cloete is convinced, and it seemed a fair call. Trouble!

Umpire Cloete is convinced, and it seemed a fair call. Trouble!

commentary: Mohammad Hafeez to Mahmudullah, OUT The Professor strikes again. Bangladesh are disintegrating against spin. Hafeez's varying degrees of spin to the fore again, he normally uses his lack of turn to get his wickets. Today, the ones that spin are doing the job. Mahmudullah was back in the crease, looking to defend a length ball outside off, but it spun in like a top on ecstasy to rap him plumb in front. That floodlight break seems to have knocked the daylights out of this chase.

commentary: Mohammad Hafeez to Shakib Al Hasan, OUT Hafeez foxes Shakib and makes it look as simple as stealing candy from a child. Tossed up, slower through the air, it lands outside off and stops on Shakib who is early on the off drive. He pops it to the right of Hafeez who pouches with glee. He gets runs, and he gets wickets. When he doesn't get runs, he gets even more wickets. What a year Hafeez is having!

commentary: Abdur Rehman to Nasir Hossain, OUT and another. Spin and the slow wicket are backfiring spectacularly on Bangladesh here. Tossed up, comes on slowly as Nasir commits himself to the cover drive, and he doesn't check the shot. It lobs into the covers, and Misbah tumbles forward to take a good catch. 69 for 1 has become 83 for 6.

commentary: Saeed Ajmal to Farhad Reza, no run there you go, the topspinner tossed up wide of off. Reza nearly bites as he looks to lash through the covers. The ball is too good for the edge.

commentary: Saeed Ajmal to Farhad Reza, OUT Reza is gone, and he's unlucky. There was an inside edge there, that umpire Cloete missed. Ajmal follows up the topspinner with a sharp offbreak that lands on off and hurtles in. Reza was pinned on the crease and the bat came around late, but he still managed to edge it onto the pad. The umpire didn't notice it, and has sent him back.

commentary: Shoaib Malik to Alok Kapali, OUT the crowd is stunned. Kapali is gone and that should be the game. Tossed up invitingly on off stump, Kapali plants the front foot across and mows across the line. He got pretty good connection on it, but not enough to clear Shafiq who wasn't fully back on the square leg fence. He had to turn to his right and back to take the catch, and it popped out in the first attempt. But he kept his cool and lunged back to pluck the rebound, a foot or so in front of the ropes.

commentary: Shoaib Malik to Elias Sunny, OUT cleaned him up! Sunny is squared up by grip and spin, and is left groping as the ball breaks past and disturbs spin. This dismissal complements the Tamim wicket at the start of the innings. Sums up Bangladesh's day. They have been squared, and quartered, by Pakistan's spin.

commentary: Shoaib Malik to Shafiul Islam, OUT And then there were none. Shafiul looks to lash to the leg side as a length ball spins in sharply and breaks the stumps. Malik looks relieved, Misbah smiles like a Cheshire cat, and the crowd looks distraught. Pakistan have swept the series.
